# HarmonyOS Launch And Runtime Rules

## Launch Model

- `app-center` is the default desktop entry.
- Other apps are hidden from the desktop by default.
- `app-center -> child app` can trigger a HarmonyOS system confirmation dialog.
- `child app -> app-center` is the preferred lower-friction return flow.

## UX Constraints

- The system confirmation dialog is controlled by HarmonyOS.
- App code cannot reliably remove or restyle that system dialog.
- App-owned UX should instead focus on clear launch wording, return-path consistency, and sound cues.

## Current Runtime Details

- Child apps currently include `EntryAbility`, `AppBridgeService`, `Index.ets`, and `SoundEffectPlayer.ets`.
- Local short sound effects exist for open and return actions.
- App launch relationships should be read from each app’s `app.json`.

## Scaling Rule

- When new apps are added, keep the center-orchestrated launch model unless the product architecture explicitly changes.
- New apps should follow the same hidden-by-default pattern unless desktop visibility is intentionally required.
